@startuml E-commerce Site User Flow Diagram

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #F8F9FA
  BorderColor #2C3E50
  BorderThickness 2
  FontColor #2C3E50
  FontSize 12
  FontStyle bold
  ArrowColor #34495E
  ArrowFontColor #2C3E50
  ArrowThickness 2
}

title E-commerce Website User Flow Diagram
header University Project - User Navigation Flow
footer Page 1 of 1

state "Homepage" as home
state "Product Listing" as listing
state "Search Results" as search
state "Product Detail" as detail
state "Shopping Cart" as cart
state "Customer Information" as customer
state "Shipping Address" as shipping
state "Shipping Method" as method
state "Order Summary" as summary
state "Order Confirmation" as confirmation

note top of home
  **Entry Point**
  Global navigation available:
  - Category selection (header)
  - Search functionality
end note

[*] --> home : User enters site

home --> listing : Browse Category\n(via header)
home --> search : Search Product
home --> detail : Featured Product

search --> listing : View Results
search --> home : Clear Search

listing --> detail : Select Product
listing --> listing : Filter/Sort\nChange Category
listing --> home : Return Home

detail --> cart : Add to Cart
detail --> listing : Back to Listing
detail --> detail : View Recommended\nProduct
detail --> home : Return Home

note right of detail
  **Product Actions**
  - View details
  - Add to cart
  - Browse recommendations
end note

cart --> customer : Proceed to\nCheckout
cart --> listing : Continue\nShopping
cart --> cart : Update\nQuantities

note top of customer
  **Checkout Process**
  Sequential flow - all steps required
end note

customer --> shipping : Continue
shipping --> method : Continue
method --> summary : Continue
summary --> confirmation : Confirm\nOrder

confirmation --> home : Return Home
confirmation --> [*] : Exit Site

legend right
  |= Symbol |= Meaning |
  | → | User navigation |
  | State | Page/Screen |

  **Navigation Notes:**
  • Categories accessible globally via header
  • Multiple paths to Product Detail
  • Checkout is linear process
endlegend

@enduml